
[1]ambrosial

   AMBRO'SIAL, a. ambro'zhal. Partaking of the nature or qualities of
   ambrosia; fragrant; delighting the taste or smell; as, ambrosial dews.
   Ben Jonson uses ambrosiac in a like sense, and Bailey has ambrosian,
   but these seem not to be warranted by usage.
